  "title": "Landscape Technician",
  "description": "<ul>\n  <li>Grow, maintain and transplant      flowers, shrubs and trees</li>\n  <li>Maintenance and installation of      sprinkler systems</li>\n  <li>Construct walkways, walls and      small foot bridges</li>\n  <li>Follows plans and specifications,      inspects and directs the planting of landscape material associated with      improvement, beautification, and erosion control</li>\n  <li>Create and adhere to various      watering and feeding schedules</li>\n  <li>Plan new growth planting patterns      in distinct seasonal changes</li>\n  <li>Identify detrimental insects or      plant disease and eliminate them</li>\n  <li>Ability to adhere to a      predetermined budget</li>\n  <li>Operate a variety of mechanical      equipment</li>\n  <li>If certified or under the      supervision of a certified applicator will apply chemicals</li>\n</ul>\n<p><strong>Requirement</strong></p>\n<ul>\n  <li>Primary/Secondary/’O’      Level Education with relevant landscape gardening experience.</li>\n  <li>With      WSQ Landscape Operation (Entry Level) Certification will be an advantage.</li>\n  <li>No      age limit with ability to work outdoors.</li>\n  <li>Physically      fit to handle tools and move around easily during work.</li>\n</ul>\n<p>Working Hours and Office Location:</p>\n<p>· 5.5-day work week</p>\n<p>· Office location: Mandai Estate</p>\n<p>· Work location: Various Sites</p>",
